The paper focuses on improving dataset retrieval in search engines, which involves information retrieval (IR) techniques such as ranking and relevance. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves working with dataset tables and generating schema labels, which are related to database (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The mixed ranking model and use of machine learning techniques for improving retrieval suggest a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.DL) sub-categories.
